items.name: SeekAstral
items.description:
Hi again and welcome to SeekAstral!


"SeekAstral" is part of my personal stylish "Seek" series where I aim to create a more overall style instead of an specific one oriented more for characters only, objects only, landscapes only, etc.

SeekAstral aims to create Sci-Fi and Fantasy aesthetics for your characters, interesting suits and armors, contrasted colors, semi-abstract backgrounds and much more. The style aims to illustration-lineart.

Main token is d3x3d and class is style so you can use d3x3d Style or just d3x3d.

How to use this LORA?

*************************

You can refer to the sample images I upload in the post but:

- For characters d3x3d style Portrait/side portrait of concept... / a d3x3d style concept...

- For landscape and objects d3x3d style concept...

Which are the best values?

*******************************

- You can go from 0.6/0.7 onwards till 1 and 1 onwards for a more "Astral style".

If you are focusing on landscapes I'd recommend 1.1/1.2 strenght and for characters 0.8-1. Of course all depends on model used and prompt.



Which models are good for this LORA?

********************************************

- Tested on 10 different models except on (as always) Realistic Vision but I'd recommend Colorful, Ghostmix, RevAnimated, Dreamshaper, etc.

This LORA is GOOD for:

******************************

- Contrasted and lighting landscapes

- Characters wearing sci-fi aesthehic clothing

- Masks

- Vibrant colors in general

- Animal robots / animal mixed / animal with sci-fi aesthetics

- Galactic and abstract backgrounds


This LORA is NOT designed for:

***********************************

- Realistic things (maybe) since it's trained on illustrations mostly.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

As always thanks to everyone reviewing, giving feedback , commenting and supportin us in Patreon. Keep supporting us so we can keep creating and delivering quality content.

David.

items.name: John Blanche Style
items.description:
John Blanche is a British artist and illustrator known for his work in the field of fantasy and science fiction art.

His style can be described as dark, intricate, and highly detailed, with a focus on creating atmospheric and visually captivating imagery.

Blanche's illustrations often depict fantastical creatures, grim landscapes, and dystopian settings, capturing a sense of otherworldly beauty and unease.

He has a distinct ability to create evocative and narrative-driven artworks, with a strong emphasis on storytelling and the depiction of characters.

Blanche's use of contrasting tones, textures, and dramatic lighting adds depth and intensity to his illustrations, bringing them to life.

His art has made a significant impact in the realms of tabletop gaming, particularly in his extensive work for Games Workshop, where he has contributed to the visual design of various game systems, such as Warhammer and Warhammer 40,000.

John Blanche's unique artistic style has influenced and inspired numerous artists and enthusiasts within the fantasy and science fiction genres.

items.name: John Constable Style
items.description:
John Constable was an English landscape painter of the Romantic period.

His style can be described as naturalistic and highly detailed, capturing the beauty of the English countryside with a focus on light, atmosphere, and the changing seasons.

Constable's paintings often depicted rural scenes, including meadows, rivers, and clouds, showcasing his deep connection to nature.

He had a keen observational eye, capturing the subtle nuances of light and weather conditions, which brought a sense of realism and a feeling of being present in the landscape.

Constable's brushwork was expressive and energetic, conveying a sense of movement and vitality.

His dedication to capturing the essence of the English landscape influenced future generations of landscape painters and contributed to the development of Impressionism.

John Constable's paintings continue to be celebrated for their evocative portrayals of nature and their enduring influence on the genre of landscape painting.

items.name: John Everett Millais Style
items.description:
John Everett Millais was an English painter and one of the founding members of the Pre-Raphaelite Brotherhood.

His style can be described as highly detailed, precise, and characterized by vibrant colors.

Millais's paintings often depicted literary, historical, and biblical subjects with a meticulous attention to detail and a focus on naturalistic representation.

He had a remarkable ability to capture the play of light and create a sense of depth, bringing his subjects to life with a sense of realism.

Millais's works displayed a strong emotional and narrative quality, often conveying poignant moments and intricate storytelling.

His art played a significant role in the development of the Pre-Raphaelite movement, challenging the prevailing artistic conventions of his time.

John Everett Millais's contributions to the art world have left a lasting impact, and his paintings continue to be admired for their technical skill and evocative storytelling.

items.name: 兼容绝大多数模型的Q版_Chibi compatible with all models_ミニキャラ
items.description:
Q版_chibi｜LiblibAI

欢迎大家去lib在线生图返图和下载，毕竟他们是真的要给我小钱钱

底层还是纸片人哈，适配动漫的大模型和Lora哈，纸片人Lora权重有些可以1，有些适当降一降，跑的时候自己测一测就好。

所有的情况下，我这个chibi，Lora的权重都是1哈(7.8，测出来不是1也一样能有效果，最低0.5吧)

我主要是想跑一跑真人的效果，所以主要测的真人

测试3D和真人大模型的时候用了一下几种组合，产生了不同的效果，我跑图一般通用tag有两套，一套跑真人，一套跑纸片人。

真人tag+真人大模型+纸片人Lora，这个需要吧纸片人Lora的权重降到很低，大概0.4这个样子，出图效果还行吧

真人tag+真人和3D大模型+真人Lora，这个需要吧真人Lora的权重降到很低，也差不多是0.4这个样子，出图效果感觉比纸片人好一些

真人tag+真人大模型，这个没用Lora了哈，效果感觉比刚才两个都要好

真人tag+3D大模型（就是国风3、NED，这种）效果最好的

纸片人tag+真人大模型+纸片人Lora，纸片人Lora的权重0.7左右就好了，效果比较平面了

纸片人tag+真人和3D大模型+真人Lora，真人Lora权重0.7左右哈，这个效果很不错，但是有些真人大模型出图也有点平面

纸片人tag+真人大模型，这个效果也很不错，但是有些真人大模型出图也有点平面

纸片人tag+3D大模型，这个效果比较不错，介于平面和立体之间吧

有些图出来有点恐怖谷效应，真不知道这个大头娃娃有什么好要审核的，大多数图片都没过

后面很多图是没带背景的，准备养点图，周末再炼一个纯粹的3D的Lora。

后面几张图没有写负面tag，居然效果还很不错，哈哈哈哈

Ps.我测了炼的各种各样的Lora，不只是今天这一个，xxmix真是出图效果最好的

items.description:
Discover MY ABOUT & LINKS to find more my models and art.

Embedding of Nina (aka Aoi) bestseller real sized silicone doll head produced by DSdoll (aka EXdoll) Chinese lovedoll manufacturer. This head mostly compatible with DS145 (aka UT145, arte145) bodies. For training I chose close up SFW photos of Nina with reddish brown or black eyes and brunet or black wigs. Nina has very interesting and cute look with big eyes and very small nose. She is on half way between real person and anime character.

Embedding trained for 1000 steps on 'v1-5-pruned-emaonly' checkpoint, so it should works well with most of v1.5 forks and mixes. I used dataset of 48 images with 680x680 resolution, and learning rate: "0.05:10, 0.02:20, 0.01:60, 0.005:200, 0.002:500, 0.001". Personal likeness was reached at 30 steps.

If you want to force Nina to looks like a real person, I recommend to use this embedding with [ ] for reduce doll likeness. Also i recommend to use Realistic Glossy Face Skin LoRa by romixerr269 for enhancement of skin texture. In this case prompt may contain: "[AIDA_DSnina] as beautiful girl, pretty face, (rseemma:1.1) <lora:RSERomantic_RSESofiko_RSEEmma-v1:0.2>"

Purchasing "Embedding of Nina (Aoi) Lovedoll (For SD1.5)" in MY SHOP for 1$ you can say me "thank you" for this model and achieve rights for selling images generated with it.

items.name: Ford GT-40
items.description:
I'm very proud of this SDXL model, it's everything I set out initially to make for myself with the 1.5, but never got working as I had hoped.

The training images were of a red GT-40 Mark II with white rally stripes, but it responds well to prompting different colors. I've even experimented with asking it for graffiti and ghost flames, see the example photos. I even posted a error 6 wheeler, check that out, lol

It will sometimes try to give 3 stripes instead of 2, and I find that specifying "white rally stripes" tends to correct that.
